"is a trivial workaround.  You need only append an at sign to the end of the "
"path, such as <literal>news@11@</literal>.  <command>svn</command> cares only "
"about the last at sign in the argument, and it is not considered illegal to "
"omit a literal peg revision specifier after that at sign.  This workaround "
"even applies to paths that end in an at sign&mdash;you would use "
"<literal>filename@@</literal> to talk about a file named <filename>filename@</"
