#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8021
msgid ""
"<command>svnserve</command> allows access to Subversion repositories using "
"Subversion's custom network protocol."
msgstr ""
"当对远程源版本库使用<command>svnsync</command>时，使用Subversion的自定义网络协"
"议。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8024
msgid ""
"You can run <command>svnserve</command> as a standalone server process (for "
"clients that are using the <literal>svn://</literal> access method); you can "
"have a daemon such as <command>inetd</command> or <command>xinetd</command> "
"launch it for you on demand (also for <literal>svn://</literal>), or you can "
"have <command>sshd</command> launch it on demand for the <literal>svn+ssh://</"
"literal> access method."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command>允许Subversion版本库使用<literal>svn</literal>网络"
"协议，你可以作为独立服务器进程运行svnserve，或者是使用其它进程，如"
"<command>inetd</command>, <command>xinetd</command>(也是<literal>svn://</"
"literal>)或使用<literal>svn+ssh://</literal>访问方法的<command>sshd</command>"
"为你启动进程。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8033
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Regardless of the access method, once the client has selected a repository by "
"transmitting its URL, <command>svnserve</command> reads a file named "
"<filename>conf/svnserve.conf</filename> in the repository directory to "
"determine repository-specific settings such as what authentication database "
"to use and what authorization policies to apply.  See <xref linkend=\"svn."
"serverconfig.svnserve\"/> for details of the <filename>svnserve.conf</"
"filename> file."
msgstr ""
"一旦客户端已经选择了一个版本库来传递它的URL，<command>svnserve</command>会读取"
"版本库目录的<filename>conf/svnserve.conf</filename>文件，来检测版本库特定的设"
"置，如使用哪个认证数据库和应用怎样的授权策略。关于<filename>svnserve.conf</"
"filename>文件的详情见<xref linkend=\"svn.serverconfig.svnserve\"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8045
msgid "svnserve Options"
msgstr "svnserve 选项"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8047
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Unlike the previous commands we've described, <command>svnserve</command> has "
"no subcommands&mdash;it is controlled exclusively by options."
msgstr ""
"不象前面描述的命令，<command>svnserve</command>没有子命令—<command>svnserve</"
"command>完全通过选项控制。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8055
msgid "<option>--daemon</option> (<option>-d</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--daemon</option> (<option>-d</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8057
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to run in daemon mode.  <command>svnserve</"
"command> backgrounds itself and accepts and serves TCP/IP connections on the "
"<literal>svn</literal> port (3690, by default)."
msgstr ""
"导致<command>svnserve</command>以守护进程方式运行，<command>svnserve</command>"
"维护本身并且接受和服务svn端口(缺省3690)的TCP/IP连接。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8066
msgid "<option>--foreground</option>"
msgstr "<option>--foreground</option>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8068
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"When used together with <option>-d</option>, causes <command>svnserve</"
"command> to stay in the foreground.  This is mainly useful for debugging."
msgstr ""
"当与 <option>-d</option> 一起使用时，会导致 <command>svnserve</command> 停留在"
"前台。它主要用来调试。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8075
msgid "<option>--inetd</option> (<option>-i</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--inetd</option> (<option>-i</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8077
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to use the <filename>stdin</filename> and "
"<filename>stdout</filename> file descriptors, as is appropriate for a daemon "
"running out of <command>inetd</command>."
msgstr ""
"导致 <command>svnserve</command> 使用 <filename>stdin</filename> 和 "
"<filename>stdout</filename> 文件描述符，适用于 <command>inetd</command> 守护进"
"程。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><refentry><refsect1><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8084 ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8522
msgid "<option>--help</option> (<option>-h</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--help</option> (<option>-h</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8086
msgid "Displays a usage summary and exits."
msgstr "显示有用的摘要和选项。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8091
msgid "<option>--listen-host</option>=<replaceable>HOST</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--listen-host</option>=<replaceable>HOST</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8093
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to listen on the interface specified by "
"<replaceable>HOST</replaceable>, which may be either a hostname or an IP "
"address."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnserve</command>监听的<replaceable>HOST</replaceable>，可能是一个主"
"机名或是一个IP地址。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8100
msgid "<option>--listen-once</option> (<option>-X</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--listen-once</option> (<option>-X</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8102
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to accept one connection on the "
"<literal>svn</literal> port, serve it, and exit.  This option is mainly "
"useful for debugging."
msgstr ""
"导致<command>svnserve</command>在svn端口接受一个连接，并为之服务，完成后退出。"
"这个选项主要用来调试。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8110
msgid "<option>--listen-port</option>=<replaceable>PORT</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>--listen-port</option>=<replaceable>PORT</replaceable>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8112
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to listen on <replaceable>PORT</"
"replaceable> when run in daemon mode.  (FreeBSD daemons listen only on tcp6 "
"by default&mdash;this option tells them to also listen on tcp4.)"
msgstr ""
"在守护进程模式时导致svnserve监听<replaceable>PORT</replaceable>端口。(FreeBSD"
"守护进程缺省只监听tcp6—这个选项告诉他们监听tcp4。)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8120
msgid "<option>--pid-file <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></option>"
msgstr "<option>--pid-file <replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></option>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8122
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to write its process ID to "
"<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable>, which must be writable by the user under "
"which <command>svnserve</command> is running."
msgstr ""
"导致<command>svnserve</command>将进程ID写入<replaceable>FILENAME</"
"replaceable>，必须对于运行的<command>svnserve</command>的用户可写。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8130
msgid ""
"<option>--root</option>=<replaceable>ROOT</replaceable> (<option>-r</"
"option>=<replaceable>ROOT</replaceable>)"
msgstr ""
"<option>--root</option>=<replaceable>ROOT</replaceable> (<option>-r</"
"option>=<replaceable>ROOT</replaceable>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8133
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Sets the virtual root for repositories served by <command>svnserve</"
"command>.  The pathname in URLs provided by the client will be interpreted "
"relative to this root and will not be allowed to escape this root."
msgstr ""
"设置<command>svnserve</command>服务的版本库的虚拟根，客户端提供的URL中显示的路"
"径会解释为这个根的相对路径，不会允许离开这个根。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8142
msgid "<option>--threads</option> (<option>-T</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--threads</option> (<option>-T</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8144
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"When running in daemon mode, causes <command>svnserve</command> to spawn a "
"thread instead of a process for each connection (e.g., for when running on "
"Windows).  The <command>svnserve</command> process still backgrounds itself "
"at startup time."
msgstr ""
"当以守护进程模式运行，导致<command>svnserve</command>为每个连接产生一个线程而"
"不是一个进程(例如在Windows中运行时)，<command>svnserve</command>进程本身在启动"
"后会一直在后台。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8153
msgid "<option>--tunnel</option> (<option>-t</option>)"
msgstr "<option>--tunnel</option> (<option>-t</option>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8155
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Causes <command>svnserve</command> to run in tunnel mode, which is just like "
"the <command>inetd</command> mode of operation (both modes serve one "
"connection over <filename>stdin</filename>/<filename>stdout</filename>, and "
"then exit), except that the connection is considered to be preauthenticated "
"with the username of the current UID.  This flag is automatically passed for "
"you by the client when running over a tunnel agent such as <command>ssh</"
"command>.  That means there's rarely any need for <emphasis>you</emphasis> to "
"pass this option to <command>svnserve</command>.  So, if you find yourself "
"typing <literal>svnserve --tunnel</literal> on the command line and wondering "
"what to do next, see <xref linkend=\"svn.serverconfig.svnserve.sshauth\"/>."
msgstr ""
"导致<command>svnserve</command>以管道模式运行，很像<command>inetd</command>操"
"作的模式(两种模式都维护标准输入/标准输出的连接)，除了连接是用当前UID的用户名预"
"先认证过的这一点。这个选项在客户端使用如<command>ssh</command>之类的管道时自动"
"传递，这意味着你很少有必要再去传递这个参数给<command>svnserve</command>，所以"
"如果你发现在命令行输入了<literal>svnserve --tunnel</literal>，并想知道接下来怎"
"么做，可以看<xref linkend=\"svn.serverconfig.svnserve.sshauth\"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8174
msgid "<option>--tunnel-user NAME</option>"
msgstr "<option>--tunnel-user NAME</option>"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8176
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Used in conjunction with the <option>--tunnel</option> option, tells "
"<command>svnserve</command> to assume that <replaceable>NAME</replaceable> is "
"the authenticated user, rather than the UID of the <command>svnserve</"
"command> process.  This is useful for users wishing to share a single system "
"account over SSH, but to maintain separate commit identities."
msgstr ""
"与<option>--tunnel</option>选项结合使用；告诉svnserve假定<replaceable>NAME</"
"replaceable>就是认证用户，而不是svnserve进程的UID用户，当希望多个用户通过SSH共"
"享同一个系统帐户，但是维护各自的提交标示符时非常有用。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8189
msgid ""
"Displays version information and a list of repository backend modules "
"available, and then exits."
msgstr "显示版本信息，版本库后端存在和可用的模块列表，然后退出。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8206
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<command>svndumpfilter</command> is a command-line utility for removing "
"history from a Subversion dump file by either excluding or including paths "
"beginning with one or more named prefixes.  For details, see <xref linkend="
"\"svn.reposadmin.maint.tk.svndumpfilter\"/>."
msgstr ""
"<command>svnadmin</command>是一个用来监控和修改Subversion版本库的管理工具，详"
"情请见<xref linkend=\"svn.reposadmin.maint.tk.svnadmin\"/>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><title>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8214
msgid "svndumpfilter Options"
msgstr "svndumpfilter 选项"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8216
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Options in <command>svndumpfilter</command> are global, just as they are in "
"<command>svn</command> and <command>svnadmin</command>:"
msgstr ""
"这个命令同<command>svn copy</command>加一个<command>svn delete</command>等同。"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: ../../en/book/ch09-reference.xml:8225
msgid ""
"If filtering causes any revision to be empty (i.e., causes no change to the "
"repository), removes these revisions from the final dump file."
